---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'May 25, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — SundayRec"
  description="Terms of Service for SundayRec software and sundayrec.com"
>
  <header class="bg-[#194280] py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <img src="/images/sundayrec_primary_gull-paa-blaa.svg" alt="SundayRec" class="w-10 h-10" />
        <span class="font-bold text-lg text-white">SundayRec</span>
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-blue-300 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 prose prose-gray prose-headings:text-[#194280] prose-a:text-[#194280] max-w-none">

      <p>Please read these Terms of Service ("Terms") before using SundayRec software and the sundayrec.com website ("Service"), operated by Richard Fossland ("we", "us", or "our").</p>

      <p>By downloading, installing, or using SundayRec, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.</p>

      <h2>1. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>SundayRec is audio recording software designed for churches and religious organizations. It enables automatic recording of services, in-app editing and mastering of audio content, and publishing to podcast platforms. The Service is provided as a desktop application for macOS and Windows.</p>

      <h2>2. Price</h2>
      <p>SundayRec is currently provided free of charge. There is no purchase, subscription or licence fee. We reserve the right to introduce paid features in the future, but any change will be communicated clearly and existing functionality will remain available at no cost.</p>

      <h2>3. Licence</h2>
      <p>Subject to your compliance with these Terms, we grant you a non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to download and use SundayRec for your organization's purposes.</p>
      <p>You may not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Redistribute, sell, or sublicense the software</li>
        <li>Remove or alter any proprietary notices or labels</li>
        <li>Use the software for any unlawful purpose</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>SundayRec, its logo, and all related content are the property of Richard Fossland and protected by applicable intellectual property laws. Nothing in these Terms transfers any intellectual property rights to you.</p>

      <h2>5. Your content</h2>
      <p>You retain full ownership of all audio recordings and content you create using SundayRec. We do not access, store, or process your recordings on our servers. See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for detail on how the app handles data.</p>

      <h2>6. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>If you enable cloud backup (Google Drive, Dropbox) or podcast publishing, your use of those services is governed by the respective third party's terms. SundayRec is the tool that uploads on your behalf; the relationship with the cloud provider is yours.</p>

      <h2>7. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
      <p>The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses. While we test extensively (the app ships with over 1000 automated tests), software is software — please verify your first few recordings before relying on SundayRec for a critical service.</p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, we shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of data or recordings, arising from your use of or inability to use the Service.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms at any time. We will notify users of material changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.</p>

      <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of Norway. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Norway.</p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about these Terms? Contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@sundayrec.com">hello@sundayrec.com</a>.</p>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="bg-[#0f2a54] py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-sm text-blue-300">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">← Back to home</a>
      <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/refund" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Refund Policy</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
